odoo... &#10;Why not have theoleptic rituals of dancing and chanting, with rare ancient musical instruments, colourful costumes, incense and flowers, and spirit possession and animal sacrifice, in school hallways. These are prayer practices of various religions... &#10;Parents of every religion should demand prayer ceremonies for their children in their religion --and specific sect-- from their school principal. Although the Principal should vet the prayer ceremonies to make sure that it is the purest form of any religion agreed upon by the religious scholars of each religion, which does not discriminate against females, that the religious practices are not hijacked by superstitious or extremist sects of any religion. But then we would have religion in the schools... I would not want to pay for that from my taxes. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1117" language="en" documentId="1426" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="angel_xy" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1426" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="61"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="62" end="307"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="308" end="560"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="561" end="1117"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>